"....... defense parimeter has been established, all defense sheilds & plas=
ma guns are functioning at full capacity."  As the computer finishes rattli=
ng off its completed tasks, Fracturcon quietly walks around his new lab & h=
ome, admiring the workmanship he put into his new research center.  "Comput=
er, download results of transformer scan into main computer.  List all tran=
sformers separatly according to Maximal & Predicon affiliation."  As the co=
mputer lists all the transformers on the planet, Fracturcon is shocked by o=
ne name that is listed on the screen.  "Dinobot?!?!  How is that possible? =
 I thought the clone was destroyed along with the Nemesis?  Computer, scan =
transformer Dinobot's spark & identify."  After a few moments of the comput=
er scanning it responds, "Spark identified as Dinobot."  "What!?!", Fractur=
con says in disbelief.  "How is that possible?  Computer reley location of =
Dinobot." No sooner does Fracturcon receive the coordinates from his main c=
omputer that he immediatly activates his booster rockets & flys out of his =
new base.  "Computer activate parimeter shield & defense grid,"  Fracturcon=
 tells his computer as he flys on a direct intercept course to where Dinobo=
t is at.  How can he possibly be alive, was his sparks actually cloned itse=
lf?  The barrage of questions flow through Fracturcon's processor like ligh=
tning but the one main question remains....How can this be the one & true D=
inobot, who sacrificed his spark to save this planet's inhabidents? Fractur=
con knew the answer to his question was not that far away.
